The White House Press Briefing on March 25, 2013 covered a range of topics including the situation in Syria, gun control, the EU deal to rescue Cyprus, the Supreme Court hearings on gay marriage, and the President's upcoming trip to Florida. On Syria, the Press Secretary expressed concern over the resignation of the president of the Syrian National Coalition, but emphasized that the U.S. will continue to support the opposition and work towards a government that reflects the will of the Syrian people. On gun control, the Press Secretary reiterated the President's support for an assault weapons ban and universal background checks, and expressed hope that members of Congress would have the political courage to vote for these measures. The Press Secretary also discussed the EU deal to rescue Cyprus, the upcoming Supreme Court hearings on gay marriage, and the President's upcoming trip to Florida to discuss the economy.